Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.48,0:00:18.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Robin!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.65,0:00:21.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can go ahead and say\Nyou wanna die or whatever,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.90,0:00:23.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but say those things... by our side!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.02,0:00:28.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just leave the rest to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.18,0:00:35.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They've come all this way\Nafter crossing Aqua Laguna.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.56,0:00:38.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you think about it, it's incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.40,0:00:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like they've at least got good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.23,0:00:42.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This time, we have permission to kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.61,0:00:45.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's easy when we don't have to\Nworry about going easy on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.53,0:00:47.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drawbridge?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.57,0:00:50.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. The Franky Family is\Ncurrently fighting to bring it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.66,0:00:55.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once it comes down, we can go\Nover to the other side at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.71,0:00:58.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez... When it's right in front of us...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.76,0:01:10.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.49,0:01:14.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously, just how terrible is\Nthe burden this woman is bearing?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.44,0:01:19.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, CP9! Listen!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.56,0:01:22.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I give you permission to kill them,\Nbut take them on here at the Tower of Law!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.83,0:01:27.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The most important things of\Nall are my life and promotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.66,0:01:34.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I let them do as they want,\Nwho'll protect me when something happens?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.04,0:01:39.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You stupid pirates!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.83,0:01:44.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get it in your heads that putting on\Na brave front doesn't change anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.01,0:01:50.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're up against the power\Nof the assassin group CP9
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.34,0:01:55.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the weight of the Gates of Justice\Nthat can't be opened by human strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.18,0:01:57.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And above all things, right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.77,0:02:01.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I have the authority to exercise Buster Call
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.15,0:02:04.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by using this golden transponder snail!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.44,0:02:06.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Buster Call...!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.27,0:02:09.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.33,0:02:11.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the power that wiped out your hometown
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.16,0:02:15.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,exactly twenty years ago, Nico Robin.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.79,0:02:21.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I remember that the following year, the name\N"Ohara" had been wiped off of the map.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.54,0:02:24.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Robin's hometown?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.71,0:02:26.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That damn masked jerk!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.27,0:02:30.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no place for me to go or go back to.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.46,0:02:33.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.90,0:02:35.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not that!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.89,0:02:39.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I like that reaction. It gives me a chill.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.23,0:02:44.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Does it mean that you\Nwant me to press this button
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.15,0:02:46.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to activate Buster Call? Hm? Does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.53,0:02:52.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really understand what'll\Nhappen when you press it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.45,0:02:59.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do. It'll eliminate the possibility of\Nthe pirates escaping from this island!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.20,0:03:02.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just with this single button.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.62,0:03:04.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's that simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.42,0:03:06.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It won't be that simple!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.80,0:03:09.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you remembering something?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.88,0:03:13.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you like, shall I try pressing it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.18,0:03:15.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right here, right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.43,0:03:22.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you doing?! Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.86,0:03:27.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure talk cocky, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.13,0:03:49.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said that "Ohara" had\Nbeen wiped off the map.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.05,0:03:52.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you see humans on a map?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.34,0:03:55.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you guys see the world that way...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.43,0:03:59.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you can do such a cruel thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.69,0:04:12.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Buster Calls are a heartless power that\Neven makes you lose sight of your goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.82,0:04:16.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't use it. Not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.78,0:04:19.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Never...! Not that!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.22,0:04:29.01,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1000)}"20 years ago - 'West Blue'\NOhara"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.68,0:04:35.42,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Get running, get running,\Nholding our flag high in the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.78,0:04:47.80,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's cross this endless sea to go in search of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.80,0:04:53.81,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,a global miracle no one\Nhas yet been able to find
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.81,0:04:58.69,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,With our hearts pounding,\Nwe'll just charge ahead as we please
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.69,0:05:04.57,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,following the footprints of\Nthose who chase their dreams
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.40,0:05:11.37,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how stormy the night,\Nif we join our hearts as one,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.37,0:05:15.62,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,we will be able to make it through
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.62,0:05:16.88,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Always!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.75,0:05:23.59,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Get running, get running,\Nholding our flag high in the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.59,0:05:29.56,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though there are tears\Nwe don't want anyone to see
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.56,0:05:35.60,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Chase it, chase it,\Nif we want to achieve our dream,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.60,0:05:38.19,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,we should always look\Nstraight ahead without fear
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.19,0:05:40.50,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't stop here
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.50,0:05:43.52,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.52,0:05:44.78,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Start me up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.82,0:05:53.52,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Get running, get running,\Nhead past everyone else
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.52,0:05:59.59,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,So long as we don't run from it,\Nwe can grasp tomorrow in our hands
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.59,0:06:05.55,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Chase it, chase it,\Neverything we see before us,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.55,0:06:10.34,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,let's carve it into the blank pages of our hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.66,0:06:13.35,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Brand New World
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.55,0:06:14.77,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Start me up!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.60,0:06:26.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Robin's Past! The Girl\NWho Was Called a Devil!"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.48,0:06:32.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Robin's there!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.70,0:06:33.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get her!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.08,0:06:36.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.27,0:06:39.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.61,0:06:41.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.61,0:06:42.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're creepy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.90,0:06:48.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monster! Monster! Monster! Monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.45,0:06:55.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahh! The monster hit me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.92,0:06:58.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's creepy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.58,0:07:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll get you for this!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.70,0:07:29.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.61,0:07:37.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My children came home crying,\Nsaying that you hit them for no reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.48,0:07:41.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stay away from my children.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.25,0:07:42.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pfft!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.21,0:07:45.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you say something?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.20,0:07:48.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez... You really are a creepy child.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.93,0:07:52.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.68,0:07:54.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not done with you yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.94,0:08:06.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mommy, Mommy, what're we\Nhaving for dinner tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.11,0:08:07.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What'd you like to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.32,0:08:09.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.49,0:08:10.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rice omelet!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.94,0:08:13.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure like rice omelets, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.92,0:08:17.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Yep!\N--We have to buy lots of eggs, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.22,0:08:18.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.24,0:08:31.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back. I'm sorry I'm late.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.23,0:08:33.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aunt Roji?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.44,0:08:46.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"To Robin. Today is..."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.73,0:08:48.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...our daughter's birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.74,0:08:53.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So we decided that the three of us\Nwould go out for dinner as a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.20,0:08:57.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's some bread,\Nso just have that for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.92,0:09:02.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't use too much jam.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.08,0:09:07.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After dinner, before we get home,\Ndo the dishes, clean the house,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.86,0:09:13.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and take the laundry in, then go upstairs early.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.58,0:09:23.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mommy, Mommy, what're we\Nhaving for dinner tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.73,0:09:25.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What'd you like to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.61,0:09:27.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.82,0:09:29.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rice omelet!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.28,0:09:32.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure like rice omelets, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.15,0:09:35.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Yep!\N--We have to buy lots of eggs, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.24,0:09:36.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.78,0:09:59.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! There she is! Robin's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.71,0:10:01.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like she came to return a book.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.68,0:10:03.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, to your positions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.23,0:10:12.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good evening, Professor Clover!\NI came to return the book I borrowed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.66,0:10:18.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One, two...!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.49,0:10:21.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations, Robin!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.50,0:10:25.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--You're amazing, Robin!\N--Just as we'd expect from a genius!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.21,0:10:27.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've got a cake for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.83,0:10:31.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Robin, the exam for the doctoral\Ndegree you took the other day...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.30,0:10:33.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You quite amazingly got 100% on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.34,0:10:36.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hence, from today on,\Nwe acknowledge you as an archaeologist.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.34,0:10:42.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now you're one of us and\Nwe'll do research together.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.60,0:10:47.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, this proves that you're\Na scholar. Take this, Robin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.39,0:10:49.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm happy for you, Robin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.94,0:10:51.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.73,0:10:58.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Robin. You must understand well\Nwhat it means to be an archaeologist.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.57,0:11:00.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Professor Clover!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.37,0:11:04.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Knowledge comes from the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.13,0:11:08.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This Tree of Knowledge is 5,000 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.17,0:11:12.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A massive amount of literature\Nhas been brought to this tree
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.21,0:11:14.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from all over the world over\Na very, very long period of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.47,0:11:19.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an irreplaceable treasure for all humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.47,0:11:24.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the biggest and oldest library in\Nthe world whose pride is its knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.88,0:11:27.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And superior archaeologists\Nfrom all over the world
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.89,0:11:30.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,gathered under this Tree of Knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.56,0:11:33.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When using these books,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.69,0:11:37.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there's no historical mystery\Nthat we can't solve.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.07,0:11:39.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got that, Robin?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.74,0:11:40.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.60,0:11:48.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to see you contribute to the\Nworld by researching various cultures.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.21,0:11:52.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor! I'd like to solve\Nthe mystery of "Blank History"!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.51,0:11:57.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha... No! You shouldn't! I forbid\Nyou to do it, just as I always have.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.46,0:12:01.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Why? If we research the Poneglyphs,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.34,0:12:04.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we'll know what happened during\Nthe "Blank Century," right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.77,0:12:07.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you know that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.13,0:12:11.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you peek into the\Nbasement using your powers?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.73,0:12:12.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.73,0:12:17.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should know that trying to decipher\Nthe Poneglyphs is a criminal act!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.71,0:12:18.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.78,0:12:23.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... you guys have been\Nresearching the Poneglyphs
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.74,0:12:25.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the basement late at night!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.42,0:12:29.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Robin! How come you know that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.37,0:12:34.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Explain yourself! Are you saying that\Nyou've been spying on that, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.30,0:12:36.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me, Robin!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.30,0:12:39.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.72,0:12:44.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you wouldn't let me in the room\Neven if I openly came and asked!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.67,0:12:52.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought... you'd let me be part of your\Nresearch if I became an archaeologist.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.38,0:12:55.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I studied very hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.36,0:12:58.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Robin...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.32,0:13:07.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that you've acquired enough\Nknowledge to be called a scholar.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.66,0:13:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you're still a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.66,0:13:14.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they find out what we're doing,\Nour heads will roll.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.04,0:13:16.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're doing it fully aware of the risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.15,0:13:21.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since it became law 800 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.17,0:13:25.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there actually have been numerous\Nscholars who lost their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.47,0:13:28.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a good opportunity,\Nso let me tell you this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.43,0:13:33.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We of Ohara are the only ones in history
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.52,0:13:36.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who managed to decipher the ancient texts.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.07,0:13:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We cannot go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.15,0:13:41.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Swear to the Tree of Knowledge!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.99,0:13:43.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you try to approach the basement again,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.70,0:13:50.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll forbid you from entering the\Nresearch lab and the library! Got that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.34,0:13:55.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Robin!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.32,0:14:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's following in her\Nmother's footsteps in every way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.03,0:14:03.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She still doesn't know about\Nthe incident from the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.74,0:14:08.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Robin's mother, Olvia, has been captured.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.97,0:14:12.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can tell what fate awaits her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.11,0:14:30.97,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1000)}"The following day"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.26,0:15:03.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grrr!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.85,0:15:18.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W... Wa...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.25,0:15:22.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Worms?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.69,0:15:32.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That hit the spot!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.07,0:15:44.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I somehow survived...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.38,0:15:48.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if she's okay, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.34,0:15:54.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm saved for now. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.04,0:15:56.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a town or something on this land?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.28,0:15:58.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.00,0:16:00.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.39,0:16:06.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I was going to drift to somewhere,\NI would've liked an uninhabited island.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.60,0:16:18.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can stay there if you want,\Nbut nothing's gonna happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.60,0:16:23.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My leg got injured, so I'll stay put here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.40,0:16:29.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm planning to make a raft or\Nsomething and leave here eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.78,0:16:33.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This your first time seeing a giant?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.03,0:16:34.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.87,0:16:40.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you, don't lump me\Nin with those guys from Elbaf.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.46,0:16:44.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are peaceful giant tribes, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.75,0:16:46.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.28,0:16:50.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know it's a long shot, but I'll ask you anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.68,0:16:56.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you get home, I don't want\Nyou to tell anyone about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.48,0:16:57.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.77,0:17:02.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was too easy. She'll definitely tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.99,0:17:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.57,0:17:13.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a lie! There's no way\Nthat a child can keep a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.20,0:17:17.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't tell because I'm not interested in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.22,0:17:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Dereshi"?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.78,0:17:36.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.76,0:17:40.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does it mean? I'm just laughing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.25,0:17:44.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're laughing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.12,0:17:47.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a funny girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.40,0:17:53.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a weird way of laughing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.20,0:18:01.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've always been told that\NI'm not good at laughing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.66,0:18:04.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're cute when you laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.92,0:18:07.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--What?\N--You should laugh more.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.13,0:18:14.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Saul. Jaguar D. Saul.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.93,0:18:16.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"D"?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.26,0:18:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I don't know why, but everyone\Nin my family has it in their names.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.27,0:18:25.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.98,0:18:27.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Robin.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.06,0:18:32.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. To tell you the truth, Robin,\NI'm being pursued right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.53,0:18:35.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So if people find me, I'll be in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.11,0:18:36.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said I wouldn't tell!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.61,0:18:41.89,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1000)}"Three days after the giant drifted ashore"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.21,0:18:49.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is yummy!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.88,0:18:51.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.47,0:18:57.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I appreciate the thought,\Nbut you go ahead and eat it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.55,0:19:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not hungry, since I caught some\Nfish and ate them during the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.27,0:19:06.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.64,0:19:11.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it'll be completed soon.\NI'll keep working on building a raft.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.20,0:19:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, you sure have lots\Nof time on your hands, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.91,0:19:24.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've been with me all day\Nlong for the past several days.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.95,0:19:26.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your friends and parents will get suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.34,0:19:30.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.38,0:19:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I do have a mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.00,0:19:35.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but she set sail for work when\NI was small and hasn't come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.63,0:19:37.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I don't even remember her face.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.84,0:19:42.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I like those archaeologists, but they\Ndon't let me be part of the research,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.82,0:19:44.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I'm being left out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.27,0:19:49.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kids in town say that I'm creepy,\Nso I won't play with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.48,0:19:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so you're a Devil Fruit power holder, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.66,0:19:57.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't scared?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.15,0:20:01.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I used to travel in the Grand Line,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.41,0:20:04.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I saw many dreadful\NDevil Fruit power holders.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.20,0:20:08.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... I envy you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.66,0:20:10.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That looks convenient!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.05,0:20:19.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really do laugh in a weird way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.34,0:20:23.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Weird or not...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.83,0:20:25.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.10,0:20:28.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...if you laugh, it'll make you happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.30,0:20:30.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.44,0:20:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Why?" When you're having fun, you laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.52,0:20:38.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means if you laugh, it'll become fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.42,0:20:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although you're only a child,\Nyou seem to be having a hard time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.32,0:20:46.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So laugh. When you're\Nhaving a hard time, just laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.68,0:20:49.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems stupid to laugh\Nwhen you're having a hard time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.91,0:20:51.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.13,0:20:57.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, you try, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.34,0:21:03.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dereshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.32,0:21:07.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! Do it like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.93,0:21:17.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's good! That's good!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.16,0:21:24.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Navy Headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.99,0:21:27.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chief Spandine, please come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.55,0:21:29.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They want to talk to you, Chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.50,0:21:32.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just ignore it. I'm sure they\Njust want a status report.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.17,0:21:36.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll contact them when we see the shore.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.90,0:21:39.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care whether it's Ohara or Opera--
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.63,0:21:43.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,why do I have to come all\Nthe way to the West Blue?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.80,0:21:45.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.62,0:21:47.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a worthless mission...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.18,0:21:53.84,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1000)}"The following day, four days\Nafter the giant drifted ashore"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.04,0:22:17.14,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We fight harder against\Nthe wall that confronts us
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.14,0:22:21.06,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We charge ahead stronger\Nwith overflowing power
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.06,0:22:25.19,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We won't fear even if we\Nhave to give up everything
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.19,0:22:28.19,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Because it's all to ensure we smile in the end
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.61,0:22:31.45,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll become No. 1
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.45,0:22:33.32,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll aim for freedom in wonderland
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.32,0:22:35.53,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, there's a faint light\Nshowing us the road to tomorrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.53,0:22:37.70,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,an era created by risking everything
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.70,0:22:39.83,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We always try our best, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.83,0:22:41.83,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,If we want to achieve glory,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.83,0:22:43.21,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,now is the time--don't be afraid
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.21,0:22:45.13,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll surely win the future\Ntogether with friends
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.13,0:22:49.09,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, we start running faster\Ntowards the vast world
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.09,0:22:53.09,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We can take off with unknown powers
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.09,0:22:55.35,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't fear, and we don't waver
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.35,0:22:59.06,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what happens,\Nin the end we'll surely...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.06,0:23:03.10,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We fight harder against\Nthe wall that confronts us
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.10,0:23:07.07,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We charge ahead stronger\Nwith overflowing power
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.07,0:23:11.32,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We won't fear even if we\Nhave to give up everything
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.32,0:23:13.32,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Charge ahead
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.32,0:23:15.20,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's start running towards tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.20,0:23:18.20,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Because it's all to ensure we smile in the end
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.53,0:23:28.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you don't even remember your mom's face?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.96,0:23:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, but I wanna see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.99,0:23:33.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is your mom also an archaeologist?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.87,0:23:37.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep. She's traveling in search of\Nthe history no one knows about.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.31,0:23:41.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What's your mom's name?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.00,0:23:42.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next episode of One Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.40,0:23:46.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Fated Mother and Daughter!\NThe Mother's Name Is Olvia!"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.02,0:23:48.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
